data.name: [TIE-56] Design Safety Meetings Technical Solution
data.notes:
NOTE: ***** SMES has a dependency on SCION *****

User Story
Problem statement: Safety Services Company currently offers its customers a product called “Safety Meetings”, a single-page document meant to provide supplemental safety awareness training for topics of interest. The current systems are error-riddled, unprofessional, and difficult to maintain – providing an inconsistent and poor customer experience.
End-goal: As a provider of this product, I want to provide customers with a consistent experience that delivers on expectations set at the point of sale. This means on-time delivery and complete fulfillment of the expected product according to selection criteria.
As a team member responsible for fulfilling this product, I want to introduce automation that reduces the burden and risk of fulfilling in the current process (I.e., I do not want to have to manually modify data in the database).
Acceptance Criteria
The solution should:
    Facilitate both digital delivery and physical delivery of the product, meaning the output should support formats feasible for both
    Eliminate on-prem server / database dependence, including:
        SSC-SQL03 (Customer database)
        Network drive (SION)
        Enterprise (SMES Application server)
        SSC-SQL04 (SSRS)
        PHXDC1
    Eliminate dependence on Gmail
    Streamline collection of customer data through use of customer-facing sales system; data collected includes:
        Company details:
            Name
            Address
            Phone numbers
            Logos if whitelabelling
            Email (if delivery through MMS remains the mechanism)
        Service type
            General Industry/Manufacturing
            Construction
            Hospitality
        Language preference
            English
            Spanish
            English & Spanish
        Subscription start and expiry dates
        Industry
        Whether meetings must be sent to multiple locations and address details for each
        Topic selections, either curated by us based on industry or selected by the customer
        Total # of meetings to receive through subscription duration or to be delivered all-at-once
        Delivery method:
            Print
            Digital
            Print & Digital
        Whether or not to include carbon copies
    Centralize storage of customer information in Salesforce and integrate with Salesforce for access to this data
    Support transposition of customer details on meeting files such as logos, customer name, phone number, & address
    Logically organize delivery of customer topic selections based on seasonality (e.g., heat illness topics sent in summer and cold stress sent in winter) and prevent duplicate topic delivery
    Automatically manage subscriptions based on expiry or renewal status
    Log shipping dates at the topic level to communicate with customers what meetings were sent & when
    Support so-called “first packages”, which are the initial sample meeting topics sent when a subscription begins before topics are selected
    Allow for changes to subscriptions including topic selections, renewals, change of industry, etc.
    Automate delivery of print jobs to printer where possible
    Support bulk mailer software, which significantly reduces costs of shipment for packages with identical weights
    Support adjustments to content of meeting files
    Scale to potential future offerings such as a mobile application to deliver meetings to mobile devices

sharepoint is what I would consider our CMS, not word, sorry. typo there

Too simplify: Input > Output > Storage; outputs the main hang up.
